AWS SDK for Java 1.7.10 This release adds support for configuring Amazon S3 object lifecycle management rules for versioned buckets and also adds support for adding tags to resources in an AWS Elastic Beanstalk environment.
AWS SDK for Java 1.7.12 This release includes an API update for the Amazon CloudSearch client.

AWS SDK for Java 1.8.3 This release adds support for Amazon EC2 T2 instances and generic request progress reporting.
This release updates the Elastic Load Balancing client with support for configurable idle timeouts and a number of bug fixes and enhancements.
Support for gzip compression for API calls. Useful for calls with verbose results over slow links (i.e. describeInstances with > 1,000 instances transfers ~ 6MB).
AWS SDK for Java 1.8.8. This release updates the Elastic Load Balancing client with support for tagging and a number of bug fixes and enhancements.
Extended DynamoDBMapper to allow more control over table name.
Fix it so that ogg files are sent with the correct mimetype header
AWS SDK for Java 1.8.9 This release updates the AmazonCloudSearchDomainClient with V4 signing support.
Support for AWS_PROFILE override, similar to the php sdk. Override applies only if no profile name is specifically provided.
AWS SDK for Java 1.8.10 This release updates the Amazon Kinesis client with support for stream tagging, and also includes various fixes and enhancements.
AWS SDK for Java 1.8.10.1 This is a patch release to address the bug found in 1.8.10 version. The bug could potentially truncate object content when retrying a upload to Amazon S3.
AWS SDK for Java 1.8.10.2 This is a patch release to address the hanging issue found in 1.8.10.1 version.
Merge branch 'aws_profile_env_var' of https://github.com/arvindth/aws-sdk-java into arvindth-aws_profile_env_var

AWS SDK for Java 1.8.11 - This release adds support for Amazon Cognito developer identities, and fixes a number of issues including a bug in RenewableCipherLiteInputStream which could potentially cause data corruption when AmazonS3EncryptionClient retries an upload.
Adding sample code to the git repo
Adding samples for Amazon DynamoDB Document API
fixing TransferManager download of versioned object
AWS SDK for Java 1.9.6 This release introduces a new client for AWS Lambda Service and also updates Amazon S3 client with support for event notifications.
AWS SDK for Java 1.9.10 This release adds support for new APIs in Amazon SQS and AWS OpsWorks, along with a bug fix for TransferManager.
AWS SDK for Java 1.9.14. This release introduces new clients for Amazon EC2 Container Service and AWS CloudHSM along with service updates to Amazon CloudSearch, Amazon RDS and Amazon EC2.
Modularisation of SDK breaks OSGi bundle imports
Fixed pom.xml to export/import correct packages
Add feature to set default profile name via system property for ProfileCredentialsProvider

AWS SDK for Java 1.9.21 This release updates Amazon ECS with support for storing and sharing information using data volumes and Amazon Elastic Transcoder with support for retrieving warnings on create/update pipeline operations.

AWS SDK for Java 1.9.22 This release updates Amazon Data Pipeline with tagging support, and Amazon Route 53 with support for retrieving the number of hosted zones and also listing the hosted zones by their names.
Avoid doing getObjectMetadata request if range is known
Support [un]registration of AdminMbean per classloader See https://github.com/aws/aws-sdk-java/issues/366

AWS SDK for Java 1.9.25 This release updates the Amazon Elastic Transcoder client with support for new conversion formats.
AWS SDK for Java 1.9.26 This release updates the Amazon S3 client with support for cross-region replication.

AWS SDK for Java 1.9.27 This release updates the Amazon Elastic Transcoder with support for job timing, AWS IAM with support for retrieving managed policies, AWS OpsWorks with support for Block Device Mapping and support for Amazon EC2 Simple Systems Manager in US-WEST-2 and EU-WEST-1 regions.
AWS SDK for Java 1.9.28 This release includes API updates for Amazon EC2, Amazon Elastic Transcoder, Amazon RDS and AWS CodeDeploy.
AWS SDK for Java 1.9.28.1 This is a patch release to address the file locking issue found in 1.9.28 version.

Expose more underlying query and scan request options in DynamoDBMapper: * select, projectionExpression and returnConsumedCapacity   from QueryRequest and ScanRequest into DynamoDBQueryExpression and  DynamoDBScanExpression; * count, scannedCount and consumedCapacity   from QueryResult and ScanResult into QueryResultPage and ScanResultPage.

AWS SDK for Java 1.9.29 This release updates the AWS Elastic Beanstalk client with support for AbortEnvironmentUpdate operation, and the AWS Data Pipeline client with support for pipeline deactivation.
prevent integer overflow when a large number of retries is allowed
Sign request after any retry pause, to avoid "RequestTimeTooSkewed" errors.

AWS SDK for Java 1.9.30 This release introduces new service clients for Amazon Machine Learning and Amazon WorkSpaces, and also includes API updates for AWS Lambda, Amazon EC2 Container Service and Amazon S3.
AWS SDK for Java 1.9.31 This release adds support for Amazon Cognito Events and support for optional delivery channel in AWS Config.

AWS SDK for Java 1.9.34 This release updates the Amazon Glacier client with support for managing vault access policies.

AWS SDK for Java 1.10.1 This release updates Amazon EC2 Container Service with support for managing task definition environment variables.

AWS SDK for Java 1.10.3 This release includes support for enabling encryption when copying EBS snapshots in Amazon EC2, support for step scaling policies in Auto Scaling and support for AWS Lambda in Asia Pacific (Tokyo) region.
